column5: A couple of guys I know, getting out a little early,but hey fishin is fishin.Hey Roy when you wanna go.....haha http://www.youtube.com/user/Smokenfish1?ob=0&feature=results_main#p/a/u/0/X7vQPjycPX0

cant believe there are no clean launches for a real boat down there... i have multiple launches to choose from here...  good for them for getting out...i was out on the 17th and it was a tough bite...
I had no idea walleye were a salt water species
It sounded like "salt water", but I think he said "soft water".

Excellent Vid Larry !!! People dont realize that there are good clean fish in the larry, so close to such a big city. Urbain fishing at its fisnest.I fish about 2 miles from there, everyday in the summer.
Walleye are a saltwater species, fish are not clean in the Larry and there are no clean ramps here. Hear what you want to hear and keep the rumours happening dudes.
Man thats hardcore die hard.  Mike
Good stuff!  You guys are lucky to have the premier fishing for walleye, smallmouth bass and musky right on your doorstep.
Going in a Zodiac in Montreal Harbour takes some gonads.....  I thought we were bad in a 14'tinny on Quinte in February???  David  aka  Superdad
